history.content:
If the class does not expand, quite unlikely. Keep in mind that the 100 people figure is calculated with respect to >500 ppl classes. With only 250 ppl in the class, it's highly unlikely that 100/250 would drop. Besides, they are going to reorder the waitlist, so you'll be further down the line. That being said, you can always hope that Listgarten and Malik scare off a bunch of people, but that would be highly unlikely too.

However, if the class does expand, you have a pretty high likelihood of getting in. If we are considering the ~500 population of normal fall semesters, everyone currently on the waitlist would get in easy. If we consider ~400 seats, then you should still be able to get in. Apparently it is unlikely for classes to expand as the department has allocated all of their funds, but 250 seats is incredibly small for cs 189, so there might be some money that the course staff isn't using yet. Of course, that is pure speculation, and we'll see what happens.

I'm currently waitlisted on CS 189 in the 105th position for Fall 21.

Do you think it's possible for me to get in? I'm not a CS nor EECS major, but just minoring in EECS. Some people told me that around 100 people drop in the first two weeks, so I may have some chance of getting in. But I'm not too sure if this is true.

I'd appreciate any input!
